President Barack Obama has proclaimed September 17, 2016, as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day, and September 17 through September 23, 2016, as Constitution Week. The proclamation recognizes the importance of active citizenship and the enduring strength of the Constitution. It encourages officials and community leaders to conduct ceremonies and programs that reflect on the significance of citizenship and reaffirm commitment to the rights and obligations of citizenship in the United States. The proclamation also highlights the role of immigrants in shaping America and emphasizes the need to provide support and integration opportunities for immigrants and refugees.